annotation.TEXT: Oh, sweet!!! I'm glad I decided to finish the level!
Two levels down. Next up is Chocolate Island 2.
Hi, Yoshi!
Hi, Yoshi!
Whoa, that was close! I almost touched the wall there! Okay, there's two left. Maybe I can hit them both from down here...
Dang, I really didn't want to interrupt the music, but with flying prohibited, I gotta do this part the normal way. Oh, well. We'll hear more of it later!
And my weapon of choice this time: Baby Yoshi! Hi, Yoshi!
Got one of them... And it would probably be faster if I just flew up there to hit the other one.
BGM: Pilotwings - Light Plane
Okay! I'm done here, but since the exit's right there, I might as well finish the level!
Now, as I make progress, it'll become more and more likely that I'll hit one of the blocks that I've already opened. This might make getting the last few a pain...
Well, fortunately, there's always this key up here that I can use!
...If I can learn to fly the correct way...
Now, flying is banned until I get to the green wall at the end of this level, so I'd better make sure I'm not at max speed whenever I jump!
Okay, now for the green block wall, I intend to use this shell to hit them all! (Also, now I can fly as much as I want while I'm here.)
Hi, Yoshi! Okay, there's little time left, so make my next shots count!
Finish!!!
By doing a Yoshi jump, I can see farther ahead, and pinpoint exactly where those remaining blocks are!
I'm doing well, but it's going to start getting tricky in a moment.
BGM: New SMB Wii - Jungle
Just don't accidentally trigger the secret exit before I'm done!
Ow. Doesn't matter, since I'm getting the cape anyway.
Bye, Yoshi!
BGM: Tetris (Tengen) - Karinka
Hi, Yoshi!
Bye, Yoshi!
Oops... Bye, Yoshi!
BGM: Marble Madness - Practice Race
Well, maybe I can't fly to scroll the screen up, but I can certainly use the vine over here!
Okay, here are the green blocks I have to smack. There are 20 of them in all.
That was tricky, and I think I got lucky with some of my throws, but I managed to do this on my first try! Awesome!
SMW challenge from mwilson90: In DP1, VS2, CI2's secret path, and SW5, hit every green ! block by throwing things at them.
There's a bunch of green blocks up in the sky later in this level, and I aim to knock them all down (or at least open them)!
Also, I've got to take care of some really annoying Chucks!
Ow. Don't care. Just move, move, move!
To the final level: Star World 5!
Just two left... I'd better take another look upstairs to see where they are, and I think I'll have Yoshi help me with that!
4-life combo! Okay, now that I've made it to the secret exit area, I've got six green blocks to take care of.
Okay, I'll just grab another cape here...
Better hurry!
That was a brilliant start...
Oh, come on. How did I screw that up! I'd better not get hit again!
I'm not allowed to touch said green blocks myself, and flying is prohibited, except at the green wall in DP1.
Ah, okay. Now I have a better idea of where to aim!
Hi, Yoshi! I think I'll take you with me this time.
Next stop: Donut Plains 1 (in case you couldn't tell).
BGM: Super Mario Galaxy - Fire Mario
Remaining:
Bye, Yoshi!
Yes! Challenge complete! Now, let's see if I can finish the level with my remaining time!
BGM: Final Fantasy 9 - Airship Hilda Garde
Oops...
I'm not going to bother grabbing Yoshi here. Maybe in the next level...
Bye, Yoshi!
Bye, Yoshi!
Man, if only I could see which blocks were left...
I decided to play this level first, since there's just one green block, and I can just quickly hit it with a shell and be done with it.
Now how am I supposed to be able to fly?
Hi, Yoshi!
Four left...
Now, as I'm tossing baby Yoshi, I want to try to avoid letting him eat any feathers...
...or else he'll grow up and become unusable as a weapon. Fortunately, if that happens, I can just dump him and get a new one!
No!!! I utterly destroyed my shell! Now what can I use to hit the blocks?
In fact, I think I'll take an intentional hit so I don't have to worry about accidentally flying.
Okay, let's whack some green blocks and get my capes back!
Hi, Yoshi!
Well, by utilizing that long red thing that comes out of Yoshi's mouth, I can reach some more cape feathers!
Now, in this level, I only have to worry about the green blocks in the secret exit path. So, let's race through the first two rooms!
And that's it for this place. I'll just clobber a few more koopas for the heck of it, then Start+Select out.
And that's that. Maybe I could've played less sloppily, but at least there were plenty of capes available here!
Finally! But, somehow, Yoshi ate the feather the instant it spawned...
